[{"object":"block","id":"38234d6d-7cea-81f2-8aaf-c5372b3d1a3e","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"38234d6d-7cea-812d-96b4-c0ce1f9c67d9"},"created_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"What’s the difference between bias and radial tires? What benefits do they provide for farmers and growers? Read on to discover how tire construction impacts agriculture.\n\nAcross the globe, radial tires make up the most of annual tire sales. In agriculture however, both radial and bias tires are used by farmers and growers depending on their field conditions, equipment, and more.\n\n","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"What’s the difference between bias and radial tires? What benefits do they provide for farmers and growers? Read on to discover how tire construction impacts agriculture.\n\nAcross the globe, radial tires make up the most of annual tire sales. In agriculture however, both radial and bias tires are used by farmers and growers depending on their field conditions, equipment, and more.\n\n","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"38234d6d-7cea-817a-8d98-f3aa727afbfa","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"38234d6d-7cea-812d-96b4-c0ce1f9c67d9"},"created_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"heading_2","heading_2":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"How are Radial Tires Different from Bias-Ply?","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"How are Radial Tires Different from Bias-Ply?","href":null}],"is_toggleable":false,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"38234d6d-7cea-81a8-8a55-eed67e8fb936","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"38234d6d-7cea-812d-96b4-c0ce1f9c67d9"},"created_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"The primary difference between radial tires and bias-ply tires is in the tire carcass and the material construction of the tires. Below are examples detailing the differences between the two types of tire construction:","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"The primary difference between radial tires and bias-ply tires is in the tire carcass and the material construction of the tires. Below are examples detailing the differences between the two types of tire construction:","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"38234d6d-7cea-81ef-ad87-ca9796fb9690","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"38234d6d-7cea-812d-96b4-c0ce1f9c67d9"},"created_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"image","image":{"caption":[],"type":"external","external":{"url":"https://maxamtire.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/question-24-1-800x571.png"}},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"38234d6d-7cea-81a8-9ff7-fca3df2478dd","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"38234d6d-7cea-812d-96b4-c0ce1f9c67d9"},"created_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Radial tires use a single casing as a spring mechanism to ensure even contact with the ground. This type of construction enhances traction as the tire’s footprint is generally wider. On the other hand, bias-ply tires are made of multiple plies of material that give the tire a “balloon-like” structure. In the diagram below, we can see how the different carcass construction changes the tire’s contact with the ground:","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"Radial tires use a single casing as a spring mechanism to ensure even contact with the ground. This type of construction enhances traction as the tire’s footprint is generally wider. On the other hand, bias-ply tires are made of multiple plies of material that give the tire a “balloon-like” structure. In the diagram below, we can see how the different carcass construction changes the tire’s contact with the ground:","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"38234d6d-7cea-811b-bd06-cd4740f285ba","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"38234d6d-7cea-812d-96b4-c0ce1f9c67d9"},"created_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"heading_2","heading_2":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Why are Farmers and Growers Switching to Radial Tires?","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"Why are Farmers and Growers Switching to Radial Tires?","href":null}],"is_toggleable":false,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"38234d6d-7cea-819c-96d8-ec4db5c024b7","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"38234d6d-7cea-812d-96b4-c0ce1f9c67d9"},"created_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"As time has passed, many farmers and growers see the performance difference between radial and bias-ply tires.\n\nThe improved footprint and traction delivered by radial tires offers lower soil compaction and better performance for farmers and growers. As agriculture equipment continues to evolve, so do the demands of the tires that power them forward. Improved tire grip, load carrying capability, and enhanced traction, are the main reasons many are making the switch.\n\nIn most cases, bias ply carcass constructed tires are built with either nylon or polyester threads to achieve a certain strength rating. Every tire is a compromise between load-carrying capacity, working speed, and the tire's footprint. By using different types of materials in the tire casing, we can enhance performance.  Here are some ways radial tires outperform bias-ply:","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"As time has passed, many farmers and growers see the performance difference between radial and bias-ply tires.\n\nThe improved footprint and traction delivered by radial tires offers lower soil compaction and better performance for farmers and growers. As agriculture equipment continues to evolve, so do the demands of the tires that power them forward. Improved tire grip, load carrying capability, and enhanced traction, are the main reasons many are making the switch.\n\nIn most cases, bias ply carcass constructed tires are built with either nylon or polyester threads to achieve a certain strength rating. Every tire is a compromise between load-carrying capacity, working speed, and the tire's footprint. By using different types of materials in the tire casing, we can enhance performance.  Here are some ways radial tires outperform bias-ply:","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"38234d6d-7cea-8147-afc3-c9b4c8b8d690","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"38234d6d-7cea-812d-96b4-c0ce1f9c67d9"},"created_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":true,"in_trash":false,"type":"table","table":{"table_width":5,"has_column_header":true,"has_row_header":false},"archived":false,"children":[{"object":"block","id":"38234d6d-7cea-816a-b7f9-f49603280651","parent":{"type":"block_id","block_id":"38234d6d-7cea-8147-afc3-c9b4c8b8d690"},"created_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-06-17T19:19:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"table_row","table_row":{"cells":[[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"MAXAM Tire Construction","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":true,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":